sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Pnif
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: promoter of Paenibacillus sp. WLY78 nif gene cluster
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The promoter of Paenibacillus sp. WLY78 nif gene cluster, We named it Pnif. Pnif is a σ70-dependent promoter located upstream of nifB. Pnif is in control of all the gene clusters of nitrogen fixation genome. Confirmation of nif promoter We standardized the nif promoter of Paenibacillus sp. WLY78, and linked it to the upstream of 3 reporter genes (RFP reporter: BBa_K1357010, YFP reporter: BBa_E0430;amilCP reporter: BBa_K1357009) to confirm the reliability of this promoter. The results are shown in Figure 2. A B C
http://2015.igem.org/wiki/images/b/b2/Confirmation_of_Pnif_AB.png http://2015.igem.org/wiki/images/thumb/3/34/C-confirmation_of_Pnif.jpeg/622px-C-confirmation_of_Pnif.jpeg Fig.4. Confirmation of nif promoter of Paenibacillus sp. WLY78. (A) Pnif+RFP reporter; (B) Pnif+YFP reporter;(C)Pnif+amilCP reporter.
The results confirmed the reliability of Pnif. The initiation of Pnif does not require inducement. Thus it is a effective constitutive promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nannan Xie
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Pnif is from Paenibacillus sp. WLY78 genome,located upstream of nifB,the first gene of nitrogen fixation cluster.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: effeciency of the promoter in E.coli for ordinary parts

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1796013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: hesA promoted from Paenibacillus sp. WLY78
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Function has not so far been determined , but Deletion analysis indicates that in addition to the core nif genes, hesA plays an important role in nitrogen fixation and is responsive to the availability of molybdenum. HesA a member of the ThiF-MoeB-HesA family and contains an N-terminal nucleotide binding domain and a C-terminal MoeZ/MoeB-like domain. The ThiF-MoeB-HesA family engage in an ATP-dependent process that activates the C-terminus of partner ubiquitin-like proteins by forming an acyl adenylate complex that facilitates sulfur transfer.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
